article.headline: Jacksonville 61, Campbell 57
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Antonio Cool and David Lee scored 13 points each to lead Jacksonville to a 61-57 Atlantic Sun Conference victory Thursday over Campbell. Jacksonville (9-7, 5-4 Atlantic Sun Conference) also had help with 12 points, including two 3-pointers, from Aubrey Connerly. Cool and Lee also had six rebounds for the Dolphins and Jesse Kimbrough had seven rebounds along with nine points. Ruell Pringle and Maurice Latham each scored 15 points for Campbell (2-13, 0-8) and were the only Camel players in double figures. Latham also led Campbell in rebounds at 12. Pringle had two 3-pointers, as did Jake Wohlfeil. Russ Gibson added nine points for Campbell.
